dividual for any transfer tax imposed under ", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "Paragraph (2)", "@value": "Veterans' Heritage Firearms Act of 2013/s:2/ss:d/p:2", "@proposed": "true"}, {"#tail": ".", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "section 5811 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986", "@value": "Internal Revenue Code of 1986/s:5811"}], "#text": "\n            "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(3)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "Transfer tax liability"}, "#text": "\n          ", "@id": "HDB44B88A53504739B869A738F5216041"}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": ", ", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "paragraphs (1)", "@value": "Veterans' Heritage Firearms Act of 2013/s:2/ss:d/p:1", "@proposed": "true"}, {"#tail": ", and ", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "(2)", "@value": "Veterans' Heritage Firearms Act of 2013/s:2/ss:d/p:2", "@proposed": "true"}, {"#tail": " shall apply with respect to the individual if the individual surrenders the firearm to a law enforcement agency not later than 30 days after notification by the ", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "(3)", "@value": "Veterans' Heritage Firearms Act of 2013/s:2/ss:d/p:3", "@proposed": "true"}, {"#tail": " of potential criminal liability for continued possession of the firearm.", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Attorney General", "@entity-id": "1500"}], "#text": "In the case of an applicable veteran or a member of such a veteran\u2019s family who attempts to register a qualifying firearm in the National Firearms Registration and Transfer Record at a time other than during the amnesty period, "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(4)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "Attempts to register"}, "#text": "\n          ", "@id": "H61EA82EC9D7B4C44A1B0EC9074D6BB60"}], "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "H32FDACD2BF4442F48C7E9DDBF50CCC3D"}, {"#tail": " \n", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "{http:/